0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"How Much Does a Deck Cost in Northern Virginia in 2026?\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img100.jpg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-09-10T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-09-10T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Nick - Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Explore the 2026 pricing breakdowns for new deck construction, materials, and labor in Loudoun and Fairfax County.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/how-much-does-deck-cost-northern-virginia\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img100.jpg","alt":"How Much Does a Deck Cost in Northern Virginia in 2026?","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"How Much Does a Deck Cost in Northern Virginia in 2026?"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Nick - Loudoun Decks"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"September 10, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Explore the 2026 pricing breakdowns for new deck construction, materials, and labor in Loudoun and Fairfax County."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"The most common question we receive from homeowners in Ashburn, Leesburg, and Fairfax is: \"How much is this going to cost?\" While every backyard and architectural design is uniquely different, understanding the baseline economics of deck building in Northern Virginia will help you set a realistic budget for your 2026 remodel."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"Baseline Pressure-Treated Wood Projects"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"For a standard, ground-level 16x20 foot deck built strictly with pressure-treated pine lumber and standard wood pickets, costs typically range between $8,000 and $14,000. This is the most economical entry point into outdoor living. However, homeowners must factor in the ongoing hidden \"tax\" of power washing and sealing this structure every two years."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Premium Composite Tier"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"When upgrading to high-end composite materials like Trex Transcend or the TimberTech Vintage Collection, the material costs increase significantly. A similarly sized 16x20 foot composite deck, featuring picture-frame borders, hidden fasteners, and upgraded aluminum railing systems, will generally range between $18,000 and $30,000 depending on elevation and complexity."}],"$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}]}]}],"$L8"]}],["$L9"],"$La"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","h3","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"Factors That Drive Up Costs"}]
5:["$","p","6",{"children":"1. **Elevation:** Second-story decks require massive 6x6 engineered support posts, increased liability insurance, and significantly more labor hours to construct safely.\n2. **Staircases:** Wide, cascading wrap-around stairs or intricate switchback staircases require hundreds of extra board feet and highly specialized carpentry.\n3. **Custom Add-Ons:** Integrating low-voltage LED riser lighting, custom dry-space drainage systems under the deck, and built-in benches will quickly elevate the project into the luxury tier."}]
6:["$","p","7",{"children":"Ultimately, the best way to get an accurate price is a free on-site design consultation where all elevations and material preferences can be mapped."}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
